
To get a copy of volume odoo10_odoo-db-data-odoo10 in the file volume.tar.bz2

odoo10:
$ docker run -it --rm -v odoo10_odoo-db-data-odoo10:/volume -v "`readlink -e .`":/backup alpine tar -vcjf /backup/volume.tar.bz2 -C /volume ./

odoo11:
$ docker run -it --rm -v odoo11_odoo-db-data-odoo11:/volume -v "`readlink -e .`":/backup alpine tar -vcjf /backup/volume.tar.bz2 -C /volume ./


To put back the file contents of volume.tar.bz2 in the volume odoo10_odoo-db-data-odoo10
odoo10:
$ docker run -it --rm -v odoo10_odoo-db-data-odoo10:/volume -v "`readlink -e .`":/backup alpine sh -c "find /volume -mindepth 1 -delete ; tar -C /volume/ -xvjf /backup/volume.tar.bz2"

odoo11:
$ docker run -it --rm -v odoo11_odoo-db-data-odoo11:/volume -v "`readlink -e .`":/backup alpine sh -c "find /volume -mindepth 1 -delete ; tar -C /volume/ -xvjf /backup/volume.tar.bz2"


Fix bug - delete the record ir_attachment from the DB 
$ docker exec -ti POSTGRES_CONTAINER_ID /usr/bin/psql -U postgres -d odoo10 -c 'delete from ir_attachment;'
